    "The \"data\" represents sensor data for each channel, \"time s\" represents Unix time for each data, and \"time str\" represents the global time for each data.",
    "The following subsections introduce the structure and composition of the dataset. cgx-aim-leg-emg.",
    "This dataset encompasses EMG values for the dominant leg, expressed in millivolts (mV), across four distinct channels.",
    "Each channel serves to characterize specific muscle information, with the unit being mV: channel 1 is designated for the rectus femoris; channel 2 corresponds to the vastus medialis; channel 3 is allocated for the vastus lateralis; and channel 4 pertains to the biceps femoris.",
    "experiment-calibration."
